RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RIVER MALBUMOONRVF took a quick lead and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was hand urged to draw off on the far turn then taken in hand for the stretch run. NICE BUT NAUGHTY stalked off the rail, gave chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and proved no match. DON'TCALLTOOEARLY settled back off the rail on the opening turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn then flattened later yards. IT'S ONLY MONEY rounded the first turn in the five path, started a bid toward the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and showed little in the lane. COLONIAL ROAD entered the first turn in the four path, moved inside leaving the turn but showed little response through the backstretch. IRISH FLIGHT rounded the opening turn in the four path, gave chase from the three eighths pole but faded nearing the far turn. SWEET T saved ground and faded through the backstretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,chased 3/8,rail far turn,no match

ENTRY.NAME: Don'tcalltooearly
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled off rail,bid 7/16,rail far turn,flattened late

ENTRY.NAME: River Malbumoonrvf
ENTRY.COMMENT: quick lead,rated pace,hand urged away turn,handily

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 28 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLACK PANDA drew clear and angled in to rate the pace, came under pressure nearing the five sixteenths pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn and held well under steady stretch handling. K K CAN chased toward the inside, raced near the rail on the turn, dug in to take second mid-stretch and just lasted. BET THE QUEEN briefly settled after coming away a bit awkwardly, gave chase leaving the half mile pole and entered the turn near the rail, angled to the five path toward the head of the lane and just missed second in a strong finish. UNLOCK chased through the backstretch and contested the turn at a close disadvantage two deep, drifted leaving the eighth pole and flattened stride. MI YAYIS chased the pace, raced in the four path of the turn and finished well outside. CAN I GET AN AMEN chased outside, raced in the five path of the turn, left the turn outside then flattened the final sixteenth. RIDE ON BEAUTY chased through the backstretch, raced near the rail on the turn then weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Black Panda
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 5/16,edge rail turn,held well driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33700. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TARAASHOQ settled inside and picked up the chase nearing the nine sixteenths pole, steadily improved at the rail on the far turn, came inside the drifting runner-up at the eighth pole, took over mid-stretch and inched clear the final yards. ADARA took over into the first turn and rated the pace, came under pressure to draw clear of Zinfatuation toward the quarter pole, drifted leaving the turn, was met mid-stretch and relented the final sixteenth. SHAKIN IT BIG TIME saved ground off the pace, bid leaving the three eighths pole and raced in the four path of the far turn and cleared third mid-stretch. ZINFATUATION steadied at the rail midway on the first turn then rated close, challenged toward the seven sixteenths pole but dropped back approaching the quarter and faded through the far turn. SHANNONRUN raced off the pace in the three and four paths, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened into the far turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 28 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JACK'S LILLY bobbled slightly after the start and settled in the three path the first turn, started a bid from the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, dueled to the front past the eighth pole and drew off the final sixteenth. PRACTICALLY THERE saved ground, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and dug in to take second the final yards. CAPTIVATING GAL drew clear and angled to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail, was met past the eighth pole and flattened the final sixteenth. IMAGINE VICTORY raced off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, came between horses two deep toward he head of the lane and finished evenly. DIAL EMMA REILLY raced well off the pace and off the rail the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn four wide and showed little in the lane. GOSSIPING rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn then weakened. VICIOUS VELMA settled inside then gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail then weakened. SARAH BELLUM raced well back.

ENTRY.NAME: Jack's Lilly
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled 3p early,bid 7/16,off rail far turn,up past 1/8,drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Dial Emma Reilly
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace,off rail,bid 3/8,4wd far turn,little lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 53. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IN THE LIMELIGHT took the lead leaving the chute and set a pressured pace, contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn and dug in under steady stretch handling to hold on. B. J. MOOSE ducked in and hit the gate upon exit, gave chase inside, raced in tight at the rail on the turn but dug in leaving the turn and dueled for second. OFFICER STONE chased outside, raced in the three path of the turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for second. GOLDEN ARROW chased through the backstretch, raced near the rail most of the turn, eased outward toward the head of the lane and improved his position. NEEDNOEXPLANATION chased the pace, raced two deep on the turn, was eased to the five path toward the head of the lane and flattened stride. TRAP HOLLER gave chase, raced in the three and four paths on the turn and showed little in the lane. HARLEY SIOUX gave chase through the backstretch but bore out on the turn and entered the stretch wide. MY PHOENIX refused to break.

ENTRY.NAME: In the Limelight
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,edge rail turn,held on driving

ENTRY.NAME: Harley Sioux
ENTRY.OWNER: Straughn William E and Thacker Daniel

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 16200. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JULY 28, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 28 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARITABLE SPENNY took the lead two deep on the first turn and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and dug in under steady stretch encouragement to hold on. EXCALIBUR rated close off the rail, bid nearing the three eighths pole and rounded the far turn off the rail then dueled through the stretch for second while gaining on the winner. HANALEI'S HOUDINI rounded the first turn in the three path and settled off the pace from the seven eighths pole, started a bid toward the three eighths, raced in the three path of the far turn and relented in the stretch duel for second. TAPPIN FOR GLORY saved ground off the pace, bid past the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. TRIPLE JEOPARDY raced well off the pace in the four and five paths, left the second turn outside and bid leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the five path and passed rivals in the lane. GEMS MINESHAFT RVF settled off the rail early, picked up the chase from the half mile pole but showed little response. OFFICER APPEAL stalked the winner inside, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced close at the rail on the far turn but weakened leaving the turn. SOUTHSIDE WARRIOR rated close to the early pace inside, faded on the second turn and showed little response through the backstretch. ELEVATED FOREVER hopped leaving the gate and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Excalibur
ENTRY.OWNER: Honoring Luke Stables and Kenworthy John C

ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus and Joy Kevin J

ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace 4& 5p,bid 3/8,5p far turn,passed rivals lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 82. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 29700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $15,000. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners O f A Race Since December 28 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since November 28 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MANAROLA chased outside through the backstretch, raced in the five path of the turn, left the turn seven wide and dug in with a burst of speed to get up the final yards. DEEMED ESSENTIAL chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail into the turn, left the turn at the rail and dueled to a brief slim lead deep stretch, though, proved best for second. ALWAYS SOMETHING set a pressured early pace, was met at the five sixteenths pole, dueled clear through the turn, dug in under steady stretch handling but was caught in the final yards. INCLUDE THE BEAST engaged in close chase and dueled from the five sixteenths pole, raced in the four path of the turn then outfinished in the duel through the stretch. AYKIZ exchanged contact with Super Wildcat leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch and raced off the rail on the turn, then flattened later yards. WILLOW MOON chased outside and dueled leaving the five sixteenths pole, raced close five wide on the turn but flattened inside the sixteenth pole. SUPER WILDCAT exchanged contact with Aykiz leaving the gate then gave chase inside, steadied in tight at the rail midway on the turn and gave way. GOT YOUR NUMBER was not a factor. DETERMINED LOVE engaged in close chase leaving the five sixteenths pole but dropped back past the quarter, rounded the turn about the three path and weakened. The Stewards reviewed, then dismissed, a claim of foul for alleged interference midway on the turn, lodged by the rider of Super Wildcat, against the rider of Deemed Essential.

ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,met 5/16,clear rail turn,caught final yards

ENTRY.NAME: Super Wildcat
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,chased inside,in tight rail mid turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Aykiz
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,chased,off rail turn,flattened later yards

ENTRY.NAME: Manarola
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside,5p turn,7wd 1/8,burst of speed,up final yards

Non-winners Of A Race Since July 28 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: JAMMIN STILL dropped well back from early contention and eased outward through the first turn, started a bid leaving the three eighths pole, circled rivals seven wide on the far turn, dug in widest leaving the turn, got up in the final yards and raced clear under the wire. JIMMY THE KID rated a short lead inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and dug in from the head of the lane, but was caught in the final yards. CAYENNE CREEK settled back two deep on the opening turn then eased out into the backstretch, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the six path and dug in to take third the final yards. KITTEN'S MAN rated close to the early pace inside, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail then flattened late yards. FRANKEE MERCH saved ground well off the pace, gave chase into the backstretch, raced in the four path of the far turn and finished evenly to pass rivals. SUGAR DADDY stalked the early pace four wide, gave chase leaving the half mile pole and rounded the far turn about the three path, but drifted leaving the turn and weakened in the stretch. HAPPY CHAMP saved ground on the first turn, gave chase into the backstretch and raced in the four path of the far turn, then weakened from mid-stretch. INTERNET OF THINGS saved ground on the first turn, bid past the seven sixteenths pole but weakened off the rail on the far turn. BETTER BOOGIE stalked the early pace two deep while between horses, gave chase into the backstretch then weakened off the rail on the far turn. THE GREAT DANSKY stalked three wide early, faded through the backstretch and was eased the final quarter.
